c 0.12.0-pre-nightly (cf1381c1d 2014-07-26 00:46:16 +0000)`, a certain symmetry breaking seems to have arisen and I want to check that this is not a bug.\n\nThe following code works in both nighty : \n\n```\nstatic myval: int = 5;\n\nstruct cls<'a>{\n  z: &'a int\n}\n\nfn create<'r>() -> cls<'r> {\n  cls { z : & myval }\n}\n\nfn main(){}\n```\n\nHowever the following code, which is a \"functionised\" version of the above example, fails in the  `2014-07-26` nightly but not in the `2014-07-24` nightly.\n\n```\nfn retn() -> int{ return 5; }\n\nstruct cls<'a>{\n  fz: &'a fn() -> int\n}\n/*\nerror: borrowed value does not live long enough\n       cls { fz : & retn }\n                    ^~~~\n*/\nfn create<'r>() -> cls<'r> {\n  cls { fz : & retn }\n}\n\nfn main(){}\n```\n\nI don't understand why the latter should not work, since if I am not mistaken, the scope of the function `fn retn()` is the same as the scope of `static myval: int`. Thanks\n", "closed_by": {"login": "artella-coding", "id": 4592812, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjQ1OTI4MTI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4592812?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/artella-coding", "html_url": "https://github.com/artella-coding", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/artella-coding/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/artella-coding/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/artella-coding/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/artella-coding/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/artella-coding/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/artella-coding/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/artella-coding/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/artella-coding/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/artella-coding/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"ur